<inglise> COUNCIL REGULATION (EEC) No 307/91 of 4 February 1991 on reinforcing the monitoring of certain expenditure chargeable to the Guarantee Section of the European Agricultural Guidance and Guarantee Fund </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EM&Uuml;) nr 307/91 teatavate Euroopa P&otilde;llumajanduse Arendus- ja Tagatisfondi tagatisrahastust rahastavate kulude &uuml;le j&auml;relevalve tugevdamise kohta </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> 4. veebruar 1991 EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, and in particular Article 43 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 43, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust (1) ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, pursuant to Article 8 of Council Regulation (EEC) No 729/70 of 21 April 1970 on the financing of the common agricultural policy (2), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 2048/88 (3), Member States are to take the measures necessary to satisfy themselves that the transactions financed by the European Agricultural Guidance and Guarantee Fund (EAGGF) are actually carried out and are executed correctly, to prevent and deal with irregularities and to recover sums lost as a result of irregularities or negligence; </inglise>
<eesti> &uuml;hise p&otilde;llumajanduspoliitika rahastamist k&auml;sitleva n&otilde;ukogu 21. aprilli 1970. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 729/70 (2) (viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 2048/88 (3)) artikli 8 alusel peavad liikmesriigid v&otilde;tma vajalikke meetmeid veendumaks, et Euroopa P&otilde;llumajanduse Arendus- ja Tagatisfondist (EAGGF) rahastatavad toimingud toimuvad tegelikult ja n&otilde;uetekohaselt, selleks et t&otilde;kestada ja k&auml;sitleda eeskirjade eiramist ning sisse n&otilde;uda eeskirjade eiramise v&otilde;i hooletuse tagaj&auml;rjel kaotatud summad; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the monitoring and detection of fraud and irregularities in connection with exports of agricultural products, products exported as goods not falling within Annex II to the Treaty and measures applicable to certain sectors or certain products must be reinforced; </inglise>
<eesti> tuleb tugevdada p&otilde;llumajandustoodete ekspordiga, asutamislepingu II lisaga h&otilde;lmamata kaupadena eksporditavate toodetega ja teatavate sektorite v&otilde;i teatavate toodete suhtes kohaldatavate meetmetega seotud pettuste ning eeskirjade eiramise j&auml;relevalvet ja avastamist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the Member States must be encouraged to take measures to step up controls in these areas; </inglise>
<eesti> liikmesriike tuleb ergutada v&otilde;tma meetmeid kontrolli tugevdamiseks neis valdkondades; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the resulting financial effort may, for some Member States, entail considerable additional budget expenditure, not least with regard to the requirements in respect of the nature and frequency of checks on goods laid down by Regulation (EEC) No 386/90 (4), and provision should be made for a Community financial contribution over a certain period; </inglise>
<eesti> sellest tulenevad finantsalased j&otilde;upingutused v&otilde;ivad tekitada m&otilde;nedele liikmesriikidele m&auml;rkimisv&auml;&auml;rseid eelarve lisakulusid, arvestades m&auml;&auml;ruses (EM&Uuml;) nr 386/90 (4) kehtestatud n&otilde;udeid kaupade kontrollimise viisile ja sagedusele, ning teatavaks ajavahemikuks tuleb ette n&auml;ha &uuml;henduse rahaline toetus; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas account must be taken of the diversity of the administrative structures existing in the Member States; whereas the latter should therefore be authorized to take reinforcement measures in accordance with differing procedures, </inglise>
<eesti> tuleb arvestada liikmesriikide haldusstruktuuride mitmekesisust; seep&auml;rast tuleb liikmesriikidel lubada v&otilde;tta tugevdusmeetmeid iga&uuml;hel eri korra kohaselt, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Where a Member State, in accordance with paragraph 2, reinforces the monitoring and detection of fraud and irregularities in connection with exports of agricultural products and products exported as goods not falling within Annex II to the Treaty, the Commuity shall, during a period of five years beginning on the first day of the month following entry into force of this Regulation, bear part: </inglise>
<eesti> Kui liikmesriik tugevdab vastavalt l&otilde;ikele 2 p&otilde;llumajandustoodete ekspordiga ja asutamislepingu II lisaga h&otilde;lmamata kaupadena eksporditavate toodetega seotud pettuste ning eeskirjade eiramise j&auml;relevalvet ja avastamist, kannab &uuml;hendus viie aasta jooksul alates k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse j&otilde;ustumisele j&auml;rgneva kuu esimesest p&auml;evast osa: </eesti>
<inglise> - of the remuneration of the agents referred to in paragraph 2 occupying supplementary posts created after the entry into force of this Regulation, which is to be fixed on a flat-rate basis throughout the Community, </inglise>
<eesti> - p&auml;rast k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse j&otilde;ustumist loodud lisaametikohtadel t&ouml;&ouml;tavate l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud isikute t&ouml;&ouml;tasust, mis kehtestatakse kindla suurusega kogu &uuml;henduses, </eesti>
<inglise> - of the cost of training and briefing agents employed on the duties referred to in paragraph 2. </inglise>
<eesti> - l&otilde;ikes 2 osutatud &uuml;lesandeid t&auml;itvate isikute koolitus- ja teavitamiskuludest, </eesti>
<inglise> - of the cost of equipping agents employed on the duties referred to in paragraph 2, </inglise>
<eesti> - l&otilde;ikes 2 osutatud &uuml;lesandeid t&auml;itvate isikute t&ouml;&ouml;vahenditega varustamise kuludest, </eesti>
<inglise> - of the costs arising from the monitoring work entrusted to the approved surveillance firms and laboratories referred to in paragraph 2, </inglise>
<eesti> - l&otilde;ikes 2 osutatud volitatud j&auml;relevalveasutustele ja laboritele usaldatud j&auml;relevalvekuludest </eesti>
<inglise> up to a total amount of ECU 10 million per year. </inglise>
<eesti> kogusummas kuni 10 miljonit ek&uuml;&uuml;d aastas. </eesti>
<inglise> The Community financial contribution shall be 50 % for the first three years and 25 % for fourth and fifth years. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;henduse rahaline panus moodustab esimesel kolmel aastal 50% ning neljandal ja viiendal aastal 25%. </eesti>
<inglise> This amount shall, each year, be allocated by the Commission among the Member States which apply therefor, in proportion to their average expenditure on export refunds for agricultural products and for agricultural products exported as goods not falling within Annex II to the Treaty, as taken into account for the last two financial years, within the meaning of Article 101 of the Financial Regulation of 21 December 1977 applicable to the general budget of the European Communities (5), as last amended by Regulation (Euratom, ECSC, EEC) No 610/90 (6). </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon jaotab selle summa igal aastal seda taotlenud liikmesriikide vahel v&otilde;rdeliselt nende keskmiste kuludega, mis on seotud p&otilde;llumajandustoodete ja asutamislepingu II lisaga h&otilde;lmamata kaupadena eksporditavate toodete eksporditoetustega ning on arvestatud kahel viimasel eelarveaastal Euroopa &uuml;henduste &uuml;ldeelarve suhtes kohaldatava 21. detsembri 1977. aasta finantsm&auml;&auml;ruse (5) (viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (Euratom, EST&Uuml;, EM&Uuml;) nr 610/90 (6)) artikli 101 kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise> However, during the first three years, the amount applied by way of expenditure on refunds shall be at least equivalent, in the case of Spain, to two-thirds of the amount taken into account for Italy and, in the case of Portugal, to two-thirds of the amount taken into account for Greece. </inglise>
<eesti> Esimese kolme aasta jooksul eksporditoetustele kulutatav summa v&otilde;rdub Hispaania puhul v&auml;hemalt kahe kolmandikuga Itaalia puhul arvestatavast summast ning Portugali puhul kahe kolmandikuga Kreeka puhul arvestatavast summast. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The reinforcement measures referred to in paragraph 1 may consist in: </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud tugevdusmeetmeteks v&otilde;ivad olla: </eesti>
<inglise> - entrusting agents with the specific task of: </inglise>
<eesti> - eespool nimetatud t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele j&auml;rgmiste konkreetsete &uuml;lesannete andmine: </eesti>
<inglise> - checking the quantity and quality of the products intended for export, with a view to the granting of refunds, </inglise>
<eesti> - ekspordiks m&otilde;eldud toodete koguse ja kvaliteedi kontrollimine, pidades silmas eksporditoetuste eraldamist, </eesti>
<inglise> - detecting and dealing with fraud and irregularities in connection with the products referred to in paragraph 1, </inglise>
<eesti> - l&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud toodetega seotud pettuste ning eeskirjade eiramise avastamine ja nende k&auml;sitlemine, </eesti>
<inglise> - entrusting approved firms specializing in surveillance work, or approved laboratories, with the task of: </inglise>
<eesti> - j&auml;relevalvele spetsialiseerunud volitatud asutustele v&otilde;i laboritele j&auml;rgmiste &uuml;lesannete andmine: </eesti>
<inglise> - checking the quantity and quality of the products intended for export, with a view to the granting of refunds, </inglise>
<eesti> - ekspordiks m&otilde;eldud toodete koguse ja kvaliteedi kontrollimine, pidades silmas eksporditoetuste andmist, </eesti>
<inglise> - verifying whether the products in question have been imported into the third country of destination. </inglise>
<eesti> - kontrollimine, kas k&otilde;nealused tooted on sihtriikideks olevatesse kolmandatesse riikidesse imporditud. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The approved surveillance firms and laboratories referred to in paragraph 2 must provide all guarantees as to their independence. </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;ikes 2 osutatud volitatud j&auml;relevalveasutused ja laborid peavad esitama k&otilde;ik tagatised oma s&otilde;ltumatuse kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> In particular, they may not, in supervised transactions or in similar export transactions, act in the capacity of exporter, customs agent, carrier, agent in the Community or in a third country, consignee, storer or in any other capacity that could give rise to a conflict of interests. </inglise>
<eesti> Eelk&otilde;ige ei v&otilde;i nad j&auml;relevalvealustes tehingutes v&otilde;i samalaadsetes eksporditehingutes osaleda eksportijana, tollimaaklerina, veoettev&otilde;tjana, esindajana &uuml;henduses v&otilde;i kolmandas riigis, kauba saajana, ladustajana ega muu isikuna, kellel v&otilde;iks tekkida huvide konflikt. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Where a Member State has one or more services, branches thereof, or agencies or sets up the same, entrusted in particular with the monitoring of one or more of the measures referred to in paragraph 2 and with the detection and prosecution of fraud and irregularities connected with those measures, the Community shall, during a period of five years, beginning on the first day of the month following the entry into force of this Regulation, bear part: </inglise>
<eesti> Kui liikmesriigil on &uuml;ks v&otilde;i mitu &uuml;ksust, &uuml;ksuse osakonda v&otilde;i asutust - v&otilde;i ta asutab need -, kellele on usaldatud konkreetselt &uuml;he v&otilde;i mitme l&otilde;ikes 2 osutatud meetme j&auml;relevalve ja nende meetmetega seotud pettuste ning eeskirjade eiramise avastamine ja asjaosaliste vastutusele v&otilde;tmine, kannab &uuml;hendus alates k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse j&otilde;ustumisele j&auml;rgneva kuu esimesest p&auml;evast viie aasta jooksul osa: </eesti>
<inglise> - of the remuneration of the agents employed by that service or agency and occupying supplementary posts created after the entry into force of this Regulation, which is to be fixed on a flat-rate basis throughout the Community, </inglise>
<eesti> - selles &uuml;ksuses v&otilde;i asutuses p&auml;rast k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse j&otilde;ustumist loodud lisaametikohtadel t&ouml;&ouml;tavate isikute t&ouml;&ouml;tasust, mis kehtestatakse kindla suurusega kogu &uuml;henduses, </eesti>
<inglise> - of the cost of training and briefing the agents employed by this service or agency, </inglise>
<eesti> - selle &uuml;ksuse v&otilde;i asutuse personali kuuluvate isikute koolitus- ja teavitamiskuludest, </eesti>
<inglise> - of the cost of equipping the agents employed by this service or agency </inglise>
<eesti> - selle &uuml;ksuse v&otilde;i asutuse personali kuuluvate isikute t&ouml;&ouml;vahenditega varustamise kuludest </eesti>
<inglise> up to a total amount of ECU 10 million per year. </inglise>
<eesti> kogusummas kuni 10 miljonit ek&uuml;&uuml;d aastas. </eesti>
<inglise> The Community financial contribution shall be 50 % for the first three years and 25 % for the fourth and fifth years. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;henduse rahaline panus moodustab esimesel kolmel aastal 50% ning neljandal ja viiendal aastal 25%. </eesti>
<inglise> This amount shall, each year, be allocated by the Commission among the Member States which apply therefor, in proportion to their average expenditure on the measures referred to in paragraph 2, as taken into account for the last two financial years, within the meaning of Article 101 of the Financial Regulation of 21 December 1977. However, during the first three years, the amount applied by way of expenditure for these measures shall be at least equivalent, in the case of Spain, to two-thirds of the amount taken into account for Italy and, in the case of Portugal, to two-thirds of the amount taken into account for Greece. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon jaotab selle summa igal aastal seda taotlenud liikmesriikide vahel v&otilde;rdeliselt nende keskmiste kuludega, mis on seotud p&otilde;llumajandustoodete ja asutamislepingu II lisaga h&otilde;lmamata kaupadena eksporditavate toodete eksporditoetustega ning on arvestatud kahel viimasel eelarveaastal Euroopa &uuml;henduste &uuml;ldeelarve suhtes kohaldatava 21. detsembri 1977. aasta finantsm&auml;&auml;ruse artikli 101 kohaselt. Esimese kolme aasta jooksul eksporditoetustele kulutatav summa v&otilde;rdub Hispaania puhul v&auml;hemalt kahe kolmandikuga Itaalia puhul arvestatavast summast ning Portugali puhul kahe kolmandikuga Kreeka puhul arvestatavast summast. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The monitoring referred to in paragraph 1 may relate to: </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud j&auml;relevalve alla v&otilde;ib kuuluda: </eesti>
